Various suburbs in Durban have been left in the dark and residents are fed up. eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Prolonged power outages have caused more frustrations for Durban residents. Some communities have been without electricity for more than five days, but the problem has persisted since December. Residents are now calling on the eThekwini Municipality to prioritise them, accusing the municipality of incompetence. READ: Durban residents fed up with unstable power Local businesses are affected as well, as they have to make other means to continue. The eThekwini municipality says the power outages are a result of cable theft, illegal connections and rolling power cuts that have a negative impact on transformers. * eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports.